question:
During debugging the following code crashes unpredictably:

```cpp
vector<int> v = {1,2,3};
for(auto it = v.begin(); it != v.end(); ++it){
    if(*it == 2)
        v.push_back(10);
}
```
What is the root cause?

A bug appears in the following code:

```cpp
int* foo(){
    int x = 10;
    return &x;
}
```
What is the issue?

Investigate the behavior:

```cpp
class Base{
public:
    ~Base(){ cout<<"Base"; }
};

class Derived: public Base{
public:
    ~Derived(){ cout<<"Derived"; }
};

Base* b = new Derived();
delete b;
```
Why might this cause incorrect destruction?

What issue exists in the following code?

```cpp
vector<int> v;
cout << v[0];
```

A defect appears when copying objects:

```cpp
class A{
int* data;
public:
A(){ data = new int(5); }
~A(){ delete data; }
};

A a1;
A a2 = a1;
```
What problem occurs?

Debug the following snippet:

```cpp
string s = "abc";
const char* p = s.c_str();
s += "def";
cout << p;
```
What issue may occur?

Consider the following code:

```cpp
shared_ptr<int> p1 = make_shared<int>(10);
shared_ptr<int> p2 = p1;
p1.reset();
cout << *p2;
```
What happens?

What problem exists in this code?

```cpp
unique_ptr<int> p1(new int(10));
unique_ptr<int> p2 = p1;
```

Debug the issue:

```cpp
int arr[3] = {1,2,3};
cout << arr[5];
```

Investigate the following:

```cpp
int x = 10;
int &ref = x;
ref = 20;
cout << x;
```
What will be printed?

Debug the code:

```cpp
vector<int> v = {1,2,3};
cout << v.at(5);
```
What happens?

Debug the following code:

```cpp
int* p = new int[5];
delete p;
```
What is the issue?

What is wrong with this code?

```cpp
int* p;
cout << *p;
```

Debug this snippet:

```cpp
vector<int> v = {1,2,3};
auto it = v.begin();
v.erase(it);
cout << *it;
```
What is the problem?

Investigate the bug:

```cpp
string s;
cout << s[0];
```
What happens?

Two functions exist:

void foo(int);
void foo(double);

During compilation they generate different symbol names. What mechanism allows this?

Consider:

void foo(int);
void foo(const int);

Do these produce different mangled names?

